The paper proposes a sparsity-based algorithm for classification applications, which is likely to fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The proposed algorithm also involves kernel methods, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. The paper also introduces sufficient identification conditions and parameter estimation procedures, which may fall under the information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories.
